-- Cotton Futures Surge by ICE Exchange Limit, Extend Rally to 15-Year High
-- B y   P a t r i c k   M c K i e r n a n
-- 2010-09-27T17:02:34Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-27/cotton-futures-surge-by-ice-exchange-limit-extend-rally-to-15-year-high.html
Cotton futures for December
delivery jumped 4 cents a pound, the most allowed by ICE Futures
U.S., to $1.0393, extending a rally to the highest level for a
most-active contract since June 1995. The fiber gained 4
percent, heading for the biggest increase since February.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
